    "content": "type: SPEC\nfiles: llama-index-core/llama_index/core/evaluation/retrieval/metrics.py\nspec: In NDCG.compute(), the IDCG calculation must iterate over the number of EXPECTED relevant documents, not min(len(retrieved_ids), len(expected_ids)). Replace:\\n    ideal_length = min(len(retrieved_ids), len(expected_ids))\\n    idcg = sum(\\n        discounted_gain(rel=True, i=i, mode=mode)\\n        for i in range(1, ideal_length + 1)\\n    )\\nwith:\\n    idcg = sum(\\n        discounted_gain(rel=True, i=i, mode=mode)\\n        for i in range(1, len(expected_ids) + 1)\\n    )\\nRationale: standard NDCG defines IDCG as the DCG of the ideal ranking of all relevant (expected) documents, regardless of how many docs were retrieved. Clamping to len(retrieved_ids) under-counts IDCG when fewer docs are retrieved than are truly relevant, inflating the NDCG score. Please preserve this iteration bound (len(expected_ids)) when integrating your relevance_scores parameter into the idcg sum.\nnote: Exact replacement for the ideal_length/idcg block in NDCG.compute()",
    "timestamp": 1783520916.3563313,
    "timestamp_iso": "2026-07-08T14:28:36.356332",
